{
  "incident_summary": "Inference gateway began returning sustained ~40% 403 error rates on all POST inference and embeddings endpoints starting at 03:14 UTC, immediately after edge rule 'geo-restrict-v42' was promoted from dry-run to blocking mode. This impacted legitimate production traffic from major customer MeridianLabs across multiple regions (EU-West, APAC, SA-East), causing batch job failures, SLO exhaustion, p99 latency spikes (12400ms), and an estimated $184,000 revenue impact.",
  "root_cause": "Edge rule 'geo-restrict-v42' (commit a4c7e2f91b3d8a5c6e0f4b7d9a1c3e5f7b2d4a6c) promoted to blocking mode at 03:12 UTC, began actively blocking requests that originated from cloud provider IPs in non-sanctioned regions (eu-west, ap-southeast, sa-east). The underlying sanctioned-list-v7 feed was updated mid dry-run observation period to contain much broader cloud provider IP ranges, causing the rule's geo-classification logic to mistake legitimate customer traffic as restricted. Dry-run missed this due to feed update timing.",
  "suspected_rule": "geo-restrict-v42",
  "evidence": [
    "All sampled 403 traces (e.g. trace_id 7a3f9c2e1b4d5a6f8e0c3b7d9a1f4e2c, 2c4e6a8b0d1f3e5c7a9b2d4f6e8c0a1b) show 'edge.terminating_rule: geo-restrict-v42' and 'deny_reason: geo_classification_mismatch: source classified as cloud_provider in restricted region'.",
    "Edge rule config change commit a4c7e2f9 (PR #4821) promoted 'geo-restrict-v42' to blocking at 03:12Z; issue onset at 03:14Z.",
    "On-call notes: rule uses strict classification and include_cloud_provider_ips=true; logic applied to regions that include major customers using public cloud VMs.",
    "Responder Priya Narayanan (author): confirms dry-run observation failed to catch the impact due to feed update on April 13, expanding affected IPs.",
    "Secondary responder (Elena Vasquez): states dry-run stats not reset after sanctioned-list-v7 update; real traffic from MeridianLabs falsely blocked.",
    "Error budget nearly exhausted, SLO burn rate 23.4x (slo-monitor, 03:17Z).",
    "Status page update and cross-org escalation involve StratosNetworks for edge rule rollback."
  ],
  "recommended_action": "Roll back geo-restrict-v42 edge rule to dry-run mode immediately, restoring prior config (commit d7f0a5c2). Request StratosNetworks apply this rollback in production. After stabilization, audit edge-policy deployment to ensure dry-run stats are reset on all upstream feed changes.",
  "confidence": "high",
